# despace

I hate whitespaces in filenames.
This tool removes them.

## Requirements

* Linux (MacOs should work as well)
* g++
* make

## Installation

Clone the directory:
```
$ git clone https://github.com/juli9797/despace
```
Change directory:
```
$ cd despace
```
Build and install:
```
$ make install
```
## Usage

Just supply a list of files to *DESPACE*:
```
despace *
#or
despace 'File to despace . h t m l'
```
